    "comment": "Rationale: Fig.5: \"Decreased dendritic spine density and mEPSC amplitude in the DG of Arf4+/- mice compared to WT mice.\"\nFig.6: \"Expression of Arf4 in brain of 4.5-month-old mice and in primary neurons, and the effect of Arf4 overexpression on dendritic morphology.\"\nFig.7: \"Arf4 overexpression promotes dendritic spine development in mouse primary neurons.\"\nFig.8: \"Overexpression of constitutively active Arf4 (Arf4-Q71L) promotes dendritic spine development to a greater extent that Arf4-WT.\"\nFig.9: \"Knockdown of Arf4 by shRNA reduces spine density in mouse primary neurons.\"\nFig.12: \"Arf4 overexpression rescues spine loss in apoE4-expressing primary neurons.\". Experimental description: - \"Genotype of Arf4+/- mice ...\"\n- \"Mixed hippocampal and cortical neuron cultures were prepared from E18-19 mice...\"\n- \"HA-tagged human wildtype Arf4 was a gift from JD Lee \"",
